Package test

Class DDPlusTest<E>

java.lang.Object
test.DDPlusTest<E>
Type Parameters:
E - The element type that represents components of the Alloy model.
All Implemented Interfaces:
IDDPlusTest
public class DDPlusTest<E> extends Object implements IDDPlusTest
Implementation of the IDDPlusTest interface for executing satisfiability checks on subsets of an Alloy model. This class utilizes the Alloy API for model manipulation and evaluation, tailored to support delta debugging algorithms by testing for satisfiability within specific parts of the model.

  • Method Details

    • check

      public int check(List<Object> chunk, List<Object> input, DataTransportObject dto)
      Performs a check on the specified subsets of an Alloy model to assess their satisfiability. Depending on the analysis type (facts or predicates), it manipulates the model accordingly and evaluates its satisfiability.
      Specified by:
      check in interface IDDPlusTest
      Parameters:
      chunk - A subset of the model elements to be checked.
      input - Another subset of model elements, used in predicate removal scenarios.
      dto - The DataTransportObject containing the current context and configurations for the analysis.
      Returns:
      The result of the check: PASS, FAIL, or UNRESOLVED.

    • removePredicates

      public String removePredicates(List<E> partListPredicates, List<E> originalListPredicates, String pathModel) throws IOException
      Removes specified predicates from the Alloy model, aiding in the analysis of predicate impact on satisfiability.
      Parameters:
      partListPredicates - The list of predicates to retain in the model.
      originalListPredicates - The original list of all predicates in the model.
      pathModel - The file path to the Alloy model.
      Returns:
      A string representation of the modified Alloy model with selected predicates removed.
      Throws:
      IOException - If an error occurs while reading or modifying the model file.
